# Fair architecture comparison

Compare candidates using more than one matching regime.

Where applicable, use:

## Matched parameter count

Models have approximately equal total parameters.

## Matched active parameter count

Models use approximately equal active parameters per token.

## Matched training compute

Models receive approximately equal training FLOPs or wall-clock accelerator time.

## Matched token budget

Models see the same number of training tokens.

## Matched storage

Models have approximately equal final encoded size.

## Matched runtime memory

Models operate under approximately equal VRAM limits.

A design may win under one regime and lose under another. Report all relevant regimes.

Do not give a sparse model more total training tokens or compute without clearly labeling the difference.

