## Chronological evaluation

Use public repository history as an evolving data stream.

At time t:

1. Expose only information available at or before t.
2. Update the allowed model or memory components.
3. Evaluate tasks emerging after t.
4. Re-evaluate all prior task groups.
5. Record storage and compute growth.
6. Test rollback.

Compare:

- Static model.
- Continuously updated retrieval.
- Structured repository memory.
- Continually trained adapter.
- Adapter with replay.
- Dynamic expert bank.
- Fast-weight system.
