# Evaluation of new mechanisms

A proposed mechanism should not be judged solely by final benchmark score.

Also measure whether it exhibits its intended behavior.

Examples:

## Routing mechanism

Measure:

- Route entropy.
- Route stability.
- Expert specialization.
- Load balance.
- Causal dependence on selected experts.
- Behavior on mixed-domain input.
- Generalization to unseen combinations.

## Memory mechanism

Measure:

- Recall.
- Precision.
- Update speed.
- Interference.
- Stale-memory handling.
- Retrieval authorization.
- Dependence on retrieved information.

## Fast-weight mechanism

Measure:

- Adaptation after one or a few examples.
- Reversion after context ends.
- Interference.
- Stability.
- Whether the update encodes useful information or only memorizes.

## Continual-learning mechanism

Measure:

- Forward transfer.
- Backward transfer.
- Average retention.
- Worst-case forgetting.
- Plasticity.
- Storage growth.
- Update compute.
- Rollback.

## Compressed-weight mechanism

Measure:

- Encoded size.
- Runtime representation.
- Reconstruction error.
- Model quality.
- Direct execution cost.
- Cache behavior.
- Gradient behavior during training.

