# Mandatory outcomes

This goal must not be considered complete after producing only documents, plans, toy examples, or microbenchmarks.

Before completion, the repository must contain evidence of all the following:

1. The previous repository state has been audited and preserved.
2. The original ideas have been reconsidered rather than treated as fixed requirements.
3. Current prior art has been reviewed across multiple architecture families.
4. An idea ledger contains multiple conservative, adjacent, and radical candidates.
5. At least ten technically distinct candidate mechanisms have been examined on paper.
6. At least three substantially different architecture families have been prototyped.
7. At least one candidate does not rely on MoE.
8. At least one candidate does not rely on quantization.
9. At least one candidate focuses on memory or continual learning.
10. A dense language model has been trained from random initialization on real code and documentation.
11. At least one proposed architecture has been trained from random initialization.
12. Baseline and candidate training use matched token or compute budgets.
13. At least one medium-scale run has consumed at least 100 million real training tokens unless measured hardware constraints make this infeasible.
14. At least one open pretrained model has been adapted using a justified method.
15. A chronological continual-learning experiment has been run.
16. Retrieval-only evolution has been compared with parameter evolution.
17. Prior-task retention has been measured after updates.
18. At least one candidate has been revised and retrained based on observed failure.
19. At least one meaningful scaling sweep has been completed.
20. ROCm performance has been measured and profiled.
21. Prototype latency has been separated into inherent and implementation-related overhead.
22. Promising ideas have not been rejected solely because of unoptimized latency.
23. Coding ability has been evaluated functionally.
24. Documentation ability has been evaluated against source-derived facts.
25. Storage includes all metadata and runtime representations.
26. Negative results have been retained.
27. All major claims are supported by reproducible experiments.
28. The final assessment identifies the strongest viable path, even if it differs completely from the original concept.

